java // Example of JWT generation in Java String token = Jwts.builder() .setSubject(user.getUsername()) .setIssuedAt(new Date()) .setExpiration(new Date(System.currentTimeMillis() + 86400000)) // 1 day validity .signWith(SignatureAlgorithm.HS256, "secretKey") .compact();

The JWT is then used in subsequent requests to authenticate the user. The server verifies the token's signature and expiration before granting access.

